message: Honored to represent my fellow Texans in Congress and work to promote Main Street, pro-growth policies to jumpstart America

This morning I unveiled my tax reform plan, Jumpstart America, to the new 115th Congress.   “My tax reform plan will simplify our tax code. It will give job creators the tools they need to succeed and empower America’s greatest asset, its workers. My tax reform plan will do exactly what its name says it will do…Jumpstart America. It's a small business perspective on tax reform, and it will benefit every American individually and our nation as a whole.”

I just joined my colleagues on the House floor to read the Constitution. I read a clause in Article 1, Section 8 which outlines the powers of the legislative branch. No better way to kick off the 115th Congress!

"Lawmakers of both parties supported the measure in a 342-80 vote, with four Democrats voting "present." A majority of Democrats, 109, voted for the resolution; 76 Democrats opposed it. All but four Republicans voted for the resolution."   The overwhelmingly bipartisan adoption of this House resolution illustrates this Congress' commitment to Israel. For too long President Obama has allowed his personal grievances to jeopardize our country’s relationship with a reliable, strategic and friendly ally in the Middle East.

Last night I voted for the REINS Act to require elected Members of Congress to authorize executive branch rulings before they take effect. This is a sure way to restore much needed accountability in Washington where unelected bureaucrats regularly draft regulations without understanding their full effect on hardworking families and job creators.

For more than six years Republicans have promised to put Americans back in control of their healthcare. Now that hardworking families have put us in control of the House, the Senate, and the White House, there could not be a better time for us to live up to our word. Obamacare was sold to the American people as a fix-all that sounded too good to be true. Today, insurers are leaving the exchanges, premiums are rising, and out-of-pocket costs have skyrocketed. Being in business has taught me that competition is what ultimately lowers prices and raises quality. We must allow people to shop for their insurance across state lines, eliminate taxes that are stifling innovation and show the nation that this Congress has a better way.

Here is my latest OpEd in The Dallas Morning News:   "I want to reintroduce competition and put Americans in control of their own healthcare plans. This means I want folks to be able to shop for their insurance across state lines so they can find plans that suits them best. But I also want to make sure those with pre-existing conditions can get affordable coverage. People should not be denied health insurance, especially when they need it the most."

For years, President Obama ignored the fact that these domestic pipelines would have created direct and indirect American jobs, helped provide energy security, and transported oil in the safest way possible. Instead of facing these realities, our former president politically cowered to a group of far left wing environmentalists who would rather see us energy dependent on other nations. As I have said before, oil, today, is the cheapest and most reliable form of energy – it will be drilled, transported and used on this planet one way or another, and our nation should be the one to reap its benefits in a safe and secure manner.

As a congressman from Texas and as a former Texas secretary-of-state, I have been to the border, and I truly believe we need an all of the above approach to border security so that immigrants go through the legal ports of entry instead of between them.   This means that we must have boots on the ground, drones in the air, and a wall where we can build it.   Secondly, American cities that refuse to enforce our immigration laws should not be handed federal dollars – this is just common sense. While we are a nation of immigrants, we are also a nation of laws, and we must distinguish between those who are coming here in search of a better life and those who are coming here to do us harm.

When it comes down to policy, Dodd-Frank is one of the most damaging laws to ever come out of Washington.  It is a perfect example of a knee-jerk reaction, authored and implemented by government bureaucrats who have never been in business. From first time homebuyers to mom and pop store owners, Dodd-Frank has made it more difficult to borrow money, it has increased the cost of compliance measures and it has forced community lenders out of business.  Community banks control a shrinking percentage of the overall banking assets but make almost half of small business loans under $1 million. In Texas alone, more than 150 banks have disappeared in the past five years as a result of these costs and government intervention.

“Mr. Speaker, I rise today to speak on tax reform. Many of my colleagues know this is a matter that I am the most passionate about. Mr. Speaker, I am a second-generation small business owner, and my daughters are third generation. I understand, firsthand, the impact that unfair, job killing taxes and regulations have on Main Street. I know what it’s like to nearly lose a family business that was built from the ground up, just because the federal government believes in a death tax. This, my friends, is a tax that strips families of the American dream they worked so hard to achieve. The inheritance tax takes money from folks who know how to use it to create jobs and donate to charities and puts it in the hands of those responsible for a 20 trillion dollar national debt. Mr. Speaker, I came up here to speak on behalf of the job creators that employ more than half of America’s workforce. These are the men and women who suffer directly from politicians’ knee-jerk reactions – politicians who have never met a payroll and have never worked in the private sector. Congress has talked about tax reform for decades, but we haven’t seen major reforms in 30 years. Well, again, I am asking this Congress and this president to act now.”

April 18 is a day when Americans of all economic backgrounds are reminded how complex and unfair our tax system really is. The irony that hardworking families have to pay money to figure out how much money to pay Uncle Sam goes without humor. For three decades, lawmakers have called for reform of the tax code while taking no true action. In that time we’ve seen loopholes and deductions created on behalf of special interests, but at the expense of Main Street America. As this Congress and administration look to tackle tax reform in the coming months, I hope and pray Washington starts to work for the families who cannot afford to contribute money to politicians or send lobbyists to DC. I encourage my colleagues and my constituents to take a look at my plan, Jumpstart America, which will benefit families, grow our economy, and put more people to work.

Ever since it was signed into law, the American people have rejected Obamacare. We saw this when Republicans took back the House, took back the Senate, and then, most recently, recaptured the White House. The only time Nancy Pelosi told the truth was when she said, “We have to pass Obamacare so that we can find out what is in it.” Today, one-third of America’s counties have only one insurer left on the Obamacare exchanges. Premiums and out-of-pocket costs have increased and choices have become non-existent. Simply put, the marketplaces are not marketplaces, they are monopolies. Time and again, Texas and the 25th congressional district have rejected the Washington style big government and socialist policies of Nancy Pelosi. She is responsible for the largest tax increase in American history, and I hope she takes some Texas values back to Washington and stops holding on to failed, broken policies at the expense of the American people.

On Saturday, April 29, 2017, the Trump administration reached their 100-day mark. Looking back, I believe President Donald J. Trump has many accomplishments that conservatives can be proud of:   - Neil Gorsuch achieved a successful nomination on April 7, 2017 as an appropriate replacement for conservative Justice Scalia;  - 13 CRAs (Congressional Review Act) have been passed under the president. CRAs allow Congress to reverse rules within 60 legislative days of their submission. This means republicans have been able to roll back many of the Obama regulations that have suppressed our economy;  - And, the beginnings of the largest and most successful tax cut and reform in American history.    The first 100 days for the Trump administration have come and gone very quickly. However, in this short amount of time, the president has made more strides for a #betterway than Obama did in his entire eight years. I look forward to working with  my Republican colleagues to help President Trump Make America Great Again!

Obamacare has failed to meet the promises that were made to the American people. Since its inception, premiums have skyrocketed while deductibles and other out of pocket costs have made having insurance pointless. Insurers are leaving the marketplaces, thereby limiting choices and stifling competition. This is what happens when government takes power away from the people. The American Health Care Act will begin to undo the damage that has been caused by Obamacare. It will restore competition, bring down costs and increase options. All the while, it will protect our nation’s most vulnerable. Today, we took a step forward in delivering on our promise to put healthcare back in the American peoples’ hands.

Zack Barth from my office is doing exceptionally well. Our entire baseball family enjoyed having him in the dugout last night. It has been humbling and inspiring to watch Zack interact with friends, family and the media these past few days. He has shown true bravery that surpasses anything I could have imagined and I could not be more proud to have him in my office and working for our district.   Thank you again to officers David Bailey and Crystal Griner. Without these two brave heroes, I cannot begin to imagine what could have been. Capitol Police as well as the Alexandria Police Department stepped up in a moment of crisis and I will never be able to express my endless appreciation to them and any other first responders involved.   Lastly, we’d like to thank everyone for the overwhelming amount of love and support they’ve sent our way. The people of Texas’ 25th district as well as around the nation have been extremely kind and generous and we cannot put into words how appreciative we are. It was evident the Lord was watching over myself, Zack and the entire team on Wednesday. We will continue to pray for a quick recovery for Congressman Steve Scalise and all those involved. God bless.

This morning, I was able to speak with the National Installment Lenders Association about what the House Committee on Financial Services is doing about the far-overreaching Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB). It was a very productive conversation discussing how we can rollback their unnecessary mandates, such as their recent arbitration rule, moving forward.

A few weeks ago, the Consumer Financial Protection Bureau (CFPB) initiated a new arbitration regulation that would cost our consumers more of their hard-earned dollars and time. It did not protect consumers and caused them to pay more for less with increasing limitations. I am proud to have worked alongside my colleagues on the House Committee on Financial Services and in the House to successfully pass a Congressional Review Act (CRA) that will rollback this harsh mandate from the Bureau. Unsurprisingly, CFPB Director Richard Cordray was thinking about one person - himself, and it was very evident in this ruling. We will continue to hold overreaching government agencies like this responsible and we will not back down until the CFPB is held accountable to Congress and the hardworking Americans it serves.

Are you ready for #HurricaneHarvey? Please share to help our fellow Texans who may be affected by the storm -   FEMA recommends visitors and residents in areas potentially affected by Hurricane Harvey take the following actions:  If the storm is expected to affect your area, know your evacuation zone and follow the direction of state, local or tribal officials if an evacuation is ordered for your area. Storm surge poses a significant threat for drowning and can sometimes cut off evacuation routes, so do not delay leaving if an evacuation is ordered for your area.  Monitor local radio or TV stations for updated emergency information, and follow the instructions of state, local, and tribal officials.  There is the potential for flooding and storm surge with Hurricane Harvey. Driving through a flooded area can be extremely hazardous. Nearly half of all flash flood deaths happen in vehicles. Stay safe when in your car by watching for flooding in low lying areas, at bridges and highway dips. As little as six inches of water may cause you to lose control of your vehicle. If you encounter floodwaters, remember – turn around, don’t drown.  Download the FEMA mobile app, which provides a customizable checklist of emergency supplies, directions to open shelters and recovery centers, disaster survival tips, and weather alerts from the National Weather Service. The app also enables users to receive push notifications reminding them to take important steps to prepare their homes and families for disasters.  Businesses of all sizes should prepare in advance for the approaching storm to prevent loss of life, property, or disruption to operations. Businesses can review and update their business continuity plans and ensure their workforce knows what to do before and during the storm. Resources are available on web sites such as Ready.gov/business and the SBA.gov/disaster-planning.  Visit www.ready.gov or www.listo.gov to learn more about preparing for hurricanes and severe weather.

With less than 30 days left in the Fiscal Year, there is a sense of urgency in Congress to provide proper aid to those affected by Hurricane Harvey. I strongly support the need for immediate disaster relief and am disappointed by Congress that this will not be a "clean" bill.

My colleagues from both sides of the aisle are willing to hold emergency-aid-funding hostage to the impending debt ceiling increase as well as a Continuing Resolution (CR). Texans and the American people deserve better than this. Their elected officials - my House and Senate colleagues - can do better than hitching separate issues to one another in order to further their own political agenda.

Since assuming office in 2013, I have opposed the debt ceiling increase every single time it came up for a vote. We should not continue to ignore the federal government’s senseless spending habits that will leave our future generations to deal with burdensome, ancestral debt. As we approach this time once again, I encourage every member of Congress to consider the lasting implications of what is going to happen when we increase the annual debt ceiling without reducing federal spending.

As history shows us, having the attitude of, ‘we’ll deal with it later,’ does not work, and raising the debt ceiling is nothing but a diversion that provides a temporary fix to an undeniable problem.   We were each sent up to Washington to make smart, fiscally-conservative change that benefits all Americans. Instead, we are increasing the debt ceiling, which is yet another Washington ploy that favors personal gain and ignores the needs of our nation.

I will do what it takes in order to protect Texans in their time of need. When it comes down to it, those affected by #HurricaneHarvey are my family, and I will fight for them. Americans are paying way too much, and keep far too little of their hard earned dollars. It’s way past time for real change in Washington, and we need to give the American people real #taxreform - we need to jumpstart this economy. Here’s my plan that is a business owners perspective on true #taxreform called, #JumpstartAmerica  Personal Tax Brackets:  We need to simplify the code by reducing to three tax brackets. The focus needs to be on relief for the lower/middle class & creating economic opportunity  Corporate Tax Rate:  Needs to be lowered to 20% to encourage economic growth & create good-paying jobs. The US is a model for creating a competitive free market system – free of a tax code that discourages growth  Alternative Minimum Tax:  We must repeal the AMT. This makes our tax code even more complicated  Inheritance Tax:  The federal government should not punish those who pass their family business or life savings onto loved ones  Full & Immediate Expensing:  Capital investment encourages economic growth & creates more jobs with higher wages  #JumpstartAmerica is smart and bold and offers an authentic business perspective, which is exactly what this economy needs.

Today, I am disappointed that Congress chose to bail out the National Flood Insurance Program (NFIP) on the backs of the American taxpayers. Meaningful reforms to the NFIP were marked up, and passed out of the House Committee on Financial Services this past June. Those pieces of legislation, some of which were passed with bipartisan support, have yet to be considered on the House floor. The NFIP urgently needs an overhaul, and until the House passes legislation that reforms this fractured program, I cannot support a $16 billion bailout that further kicks this problem to the future. I encourage House Leadership to take up the NFIP reforms passed out of the Committee, and to consider each natural disaster individually, based upon their specific needs

GOOD NEWS → the House just passed H.R. 849, the Protecting Seniors’ Access to Medicare Act. The current healthcare law created a new federal agency called the Independent Payment Advisory Board (IPAB) that has the authority to unilaterally cut Medicare spending. This bill will repeal IPAB, and is another step in the right direction to rolling back the failed #Obamacare  ✔ We’re putting the needs of the patient at the center of our health care system  ✔ This positively impacts the quality and access to medical care for seniors  ✔ Significant bipartisan support  Republicans and Democrats agree that allowing a panel of Washington bureaucrats to make these critical healthcare decisions, rather than patients and their families, is no way to treat America's seniors. I am proud to have voted in favor of this long overdue Obamacare repeal, and urge my Senate colleagues to take this up quickly

Today is the day! The Tax Cuts & Jobs Act overhauls America's tax code to deliver historic tax relief to everyday Americans. Here's how:  ✔ INCREASES the standard deduction for individuals and couples → this means MORE money back in your pocket ✔ Lowers tax rates so people can keep more of their hard earned money ✔ Delivers significant tax relief to Main Street job creators ✔ Means MORE jobs coming back to communities all around this country
We are moments away from the House passing a major overhaul to the current tax plan! This #TaxReform plan will change the course of our nation and empower everyday Americans

Today will long be remembered as a time when American families and businesses were once again made a priority. For far too long, Washington has taken from the American people with nothing to offer in return except constant financial and economic struggle. Finally, Congress has listened to your demands, and vowed to make a positive difference that will benefit all Americans. With the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act, the average middle-income family will see more of their hard-earned money back in their pockets  STATEMENT ↓ https://williams.house.gov/media-center/press-releases/congressman-williams-votes-for-historic-tax-reform

I have fought to bring a commonsense business owner’s perspective to the halls of Congress by tirelessly pushing forward with a framework of tax reform that would jumpstart this country. As a businessman, I am proud that much of these ideas have been included in this plan, and I applaud this Administration’s, and this Congress’ persistent efforts to deliver much needed tax relief to the American people

We promised a pro-growth, pro-family AND pro-American #taxreform plan and today, we delivered on that promise. I am proud to be at the White House this afternoon with President Donald J. Trump for this historic moment
With the Tax Cuts & Jobs Act, an everyday family of four earning $73,000 will receive a tax CUT of $2,059. What will you do with the extra money back in your pocket? #taxreform

Yesterday, President Donald J. Trump signed the Tax Cuts & Jobs Act into law. Finally, we have kept our promise to the American people by putting our broken tax code behind us.  This tax plan will spur economic growth and innovation, and hardworking families everywhere begin to see more money in their paychecks

Main Street job creators will see historic new tax relief to help them succeed and grow. This includes a first-ever small business tax deduction of 20% that will save our job creators money so they can create more jobs and increase paychecks.

After years of stagnant wages, this new tax code will finally help Americans get a raise. It will reward hard work and encourage investment in our communities to increase the growth of jobs, productivity, and paychecks for hardworking Americans nationwide

The nightmare of tax complexity is coming to an end. With this dramatically simpler and fairer tax code, roughly 9 out of 10 Americans will be able to file their taxes on a form as straightforward as a postcard
Doubling the Child Tax Credit from $1,000 to $2,000 will help more parents across the country with the costs of raising a family and caring for loved ones

With lower tax rates at all income levels, Americans in every community will be able to keep more of their hard-earned money to save or spend as they see fit. In fact, a family of four earning the median family income of $73,000 will save over $2,000.
